Statistical Transformation

ggplot(diamonds) + 
  stat_summary(
    mapping = aes(x = cut, y = depth),
    fun.min = min,
    fun.max = max,
    fun = median
  )

demo <- tribble(
  ~a,~b,
  "1", 20,
  "2" , 15,
  "3", 45
)

ggplot(demo, mapping = aes(x = a, y = b)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity")

ggplot(diamonds ) +
  geom_bar(aes(x = cut, fill = clarity))

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x = cut, y = depth)) +
  stat_summary(
    fun.ymin = min,
    fun.ymax = max,
    fun = median
  )
## Warning: `fun.ymin` is deprecated. Use `fun.min` instead.
## Warning: `fun.ymax` is deprecated. Use `fun.max` instead.

Position Adjustments

ggplot(diamonds) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, color = cut))

ggplot(diamonds) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = cut))

ggplot(diamonds) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes( x = cut, fill = clarity))

## Position Adjustments

In the above chart, the position is automatically set to stacking. This can be replaced with identity, dodge, or fill.

Identity

ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity)) +
  geom_bar(alpha = 1/2, position = "identity")

ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, color = clarity)) +
  geom_bar(fill = NA, position = "identity")

### Fill

ggplot(diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity)) +
  geom_bar(position = "fill")

Dodge

ggplot(diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity)) +
  geom_bar(position = "dodge")

Jitter

ggplot(mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))+
  geom_point(position = "jitter")

for help, ?position_dodge, ?position_fill, ?position_identity, ?position_jitter, ?position_stack.
